Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle
over half the @curry powder mix{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
lid. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and 1/4 tsp salt and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways, then cut them
into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add
the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to the pan and season with salt and
pepper. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat to medium, add the @korma curry paste{50%g}, garlic and remaining
curry powder mix. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} and
@water{100%ml} for the curry. Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat, cover with a lid and simmer until the broccoli is
just tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @mango chutney{40%g}. Bring back to the boil,
then remove from the heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if you feel it
needs it.

Once the sweet potato is roasted, stir it through the curry. Return the pan to the
heat to warm through. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your plates, then top with your
chicken korma style curry. Enjoy!